279 <a href="javascript:card_browser(163)">Thin and Stretched</a> (Rare)<br>
  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This is mainly a strategy deck, yet I think it is quite fun as well. <br>
<br>
I will give a general description first, then a little more detailed. <br>
<br>
The first thing you need to do, is bid fairly high, since you need to pull out Aragorn-Ranger of the North out quickly. This happens by using The Prancing Pony Site. After that, you will be able to &quot;endure the evils of Middle-Earth&quot;. You would be able to make it through site 9 with this Fellowship, but I find it much easier to corrupt or overwhelm the Ring Bearer with my shadow cards. <br>
<br>
The Shadow cards are designed to let you play both Nazgul and Morgul (Sauron) Orcs at a generally quick rate of speed. Just one of the Fierce Nazgul can wreak some big havoc each site. The Orc cards have some big guns in them, which will help slow the Fellowship down considerably, and give more than a good chance at corrupting the Ring-Bearer if you get them at a decently early site. Either way, it will be extremely hard for the Fellowship to get through site 9. <br>
<br>
Now for the more detailed: <br>
<br>
Fellowship Strategy- <br>
<br>
Sam can take off burdens fairly easily, and since he is not a major player, can be sacrificed at a moderately low cost. It is a good idea to keep him, just in case Frodo is killed. <br>
<br>
Legolas is a help in picking off early minions that are sent against you, while aragorn can finish them off. <br>
<br>
Save (unless going to be overwhelmed) defiance and border defenses cards till later sites, since most likely, that is when you will need them. If they build up, use some just to renew your hand. <br>
<br>
Try your best to stop at site 3 and 6 for healing when you start your Fellowship again. If you think that you are lagging behind your opponent, then you can probably afford to skip one, or both if your Fellowship is doing well on wounds, etc. (Plus, you can heal Aragorn and Boromir with their extras.) <br>
<br>
Most of the other Fellowship cards are self-explanatory (Get Elrond out site 6 or before so he can fight twice during the game, same with Galadriel). <br>
<br>
Shadow Strategy- <br>
<br>
Beat &#39;em down with Nazgul, Burden them with Orcs. <br>
<br>
First of all, use Desperate Defense of the Ring on the highest strength/powered up Fellowship character, this does wonders for your minions. You should substitute more of these wonderful cards into ur deck if you have them, but i only have one. <br>
<br>
Most likely, you will have to use Despair near the end of the sites, but if you use your Nazgul and high strength Orcs well, as well as some other &quot;Burden&quot; cards, you might well be able to use it sooner. (Def: If there are 12 burdens and companions in the dead pile combined, corrupt the Ring Bearer.) <br>
<br>
If you use one Nazgul and maybe one Orc per Site or two at a time in later sites, you can severly hurt the Fellowship. I use only the Fierce Nazgul (except one, which you can exert to make fierce), and several Nazgul cards that require you to spot about 3 burdens (usually not hard to do). It is a good idea to save The Pale Blade for the Witch King, causing many Companions to be overwhelmed. You can also use other Nazgul at the same time as the Witch King; even one other Nazgul with him could utterly destroy the Fellowship. <br>
<br>
Make sure you get Thin and Stretched out on the Ring Bearer. <br>
<br>
The rest is self-explanatory. <br>
<br>
Conclusion-<br>
<br>
If you get stuck, discard a card and draw another during your regroup phase! This keeps the game going smoothly, and doesn&#39;t usually hurt much with this deck. Above all else, remember to have fun, and if you are beat for some reason, not a biggie! Thanks to all who review this deck, and God Bless...  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=20675"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=20675" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
